Lunaria's AD Blocker

A simple Chrome extension that blocks unwanted ads and improves browsing speed.

Project Structure

ADblocker/
│
├── manifest.json
├── background.js
├── popup.html
└── icons/
├── icon16.png
├── icon48.png
└── icon128.png

How to Install (Load Unpacked Extension)

Open Google Chrome (or another Chromium-based browser).

Go to chrome://extensions/

Turn ON "Developer mode" in the top-right corner.

Click "Load unpacked".

Select the ADblocker folder (the one containing manifest.json).

The extension should now appear in your toolbar.

File Descriptions

manifest.json - Defines the extension’s name, version, permissions, and icons.
background.js - Contains background logic such as ad blocking rules.
popup.html - The small window shown when clicking the extension icon.
icons/ - Folder containing the extension’s icons in multiple sizes.

Permissions Used

storage - Saves user preferences.
tabs - Allows the extension to access browser tabs.
webRequest - Lets the extension monitor network requests.
webRequestBlocking - Enables blocking unwanted requests.
host_permissions - Grants access to all websites (<all_urls>).

Development Notes

• Edit background.js to customize ad blocking or logging behavior.
• Modify popup.html to adjust the interface or add settings.
• After editing files, go to chrome://extensions/ and click "Reload" to apply changes.

Testing

Visit a website that contains ads.

Open Developer Tools (Ctrl + Shift + I) → Console tab.

Look for logs or blocked request messages from background.js.

Troubleshooting

Problem: "Could not load icon..."
Cause: The icon file path in manifest.json is incorrect.
Solution: Make sure file names and paths match exactly.

Problem: Extension won't load
Cause: Invalid or malformed JSON in manifest.json.
Solution: Validate your JSON using https://jsonlint.com

Problem: Popup not showing
Cause: popup.html missing or incorrect path.
Solution: Verify the default_popup value in manifest.json.

